result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason Elder Dorzok was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Avoid Penalty, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes:
lf extended supervision is revoked and the defendant will have a mandatory release from prison, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due. 

Defendant shall provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice.
Defendant shall obtain and maintain full time employment or schooling or combination thereof to equal full time.

Defendant shall have no contact with Crystal M. or J. W. B.

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety. 

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription and then taken as prescribed.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and comply with recommendations.
Defendant shall participate in all counseling, assessments, and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent, including and comply with treatment recommendations.
